⁶ Se Manlium praemisisse, &c.] Muretus, in his comments on Cicero's first oration against Catiline, p. 34, reads, Se ad Manlium prae- misisse eam multitudinem, Sec. He truJy observes, Non Manlium ad multitudinem, sed contra, multitudinem ad Manlium praemiserat. I agree with this learned critic, though I have left the text unaltered. The modern commentators are silent here—C.
